Interface VirtualView

All Superinterfaces:
Remote
All Known Implementing Classes:
RmiClient, SocketClientHandler, SocketClientSide
public interface VirtualView extends Remote
The VirtualView interface represents an abstraction for updating the game state on the client-side through remote procedure calls. It is intended to be implemented by classes that act as views for a remote client in a client-server architecture. It provides methods to update various components of the game's state and lobby details, ensuring the client remains synchronized with the server. Additionally, it supports displaying messages, game phase updates, player readiness states, and other game-related data.
